				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:322px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:GD-FR-Paris-Louvre-Sculptures034.JPG" class="image"><img alt="A large sculpture of six life-sized black-cloaked men, their faces obscured by their hoods, carrying a slab upon which lies the supine effigy of a knight, with hands folded together in prayer. His head rests on a pillow, and his feet on a small reclining lion." src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/GD-FR-Paris-Louvre-Sculptures034.JPG/320px-GD-FR-Paris-Louvre-Sculptures034.JPG" width="320" height="240" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/GD-FR-Paris-Louvre-Sculptures034.JPG/480px-GD-FR-Paris-Louvre-Sculptures034.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fa/GD-FR-Paris-Louvre-Sculptures034.JPG/640px-GD-FR-Paris-Louvre-Sculptures034.JPG 2x" /></a>
